    answer: "Published research demonstrates that for domain-specific applications, the encoder (embedding model) determines retrieval accuracy more than the generator (LLM) determines output quality. A domain-tuned embedding with a mid-tier generation model outperforms a frontier model with generic retrieval on defense-specific tasks. DLRA invests where the accuracy gains are largest."
